You were talking about Mac Prescott a while ago. I 
was thinking about some things. Everybody who

18:25.090 --> 18:29.415
lives in the administration, I think, has some 
one-liners that are really good. You were always

18:29.435 --> 18:30.436
good at this. Your sense of humor was, I think, kept 
you apart. Mac Prescott was famous for saying,

18:35.101 --> 18:40.147
give me patience and give it to me now. And I'm 
humble and proud of it. And I guess I picked up some

18:44.191 --> 18:49.918
little things like that from nearly everybody who 
sat in that office. I remember

18:56.123 --> 18:59.307
Oh, who was the president that preceded Bowen? I'm 
blocking his name. Bill Mobley? Bill Mobley. Bill

19:04.814 --> 19:14.326
Mobley retired and John Coles retired three days 
before him and three days after him. And at John

19:15.287 --> 19:24.038
Coles' retirement reception, Bill Mobley said, I 
promised myself that I would retire three days

19:15.287 --> 19:24.038
before John Coles. I thought that was good. I 
believe we've, okay, let me then appoint you as a

19:28.127 --> 19:35.998
consultant. Let's make believe that you have now 
been recruited to advise the department and the

19:36.018 --> 19:50.598
college about what they're, what they should be 
trying to do next. What advice would you give to the

19:51.479 --> 19:54.143
department in the College of Education as they are 
looking toward the future?

20:03.433 --> 20:10.928
I think from the college's point of view, they're 
in a real difficult situation. Somewhere along

20:13.212 --> 20:14.595
the way, we decided that colleges of education 
were the cause of poor teaching that goes on in

20:16.448 --> 20:26.283
public schools and poor education that goes on 
there. And consequently, colleges of education

20:26.804 --> 20:31.210
are just hanging on by their fingertips.

20:33.714 --> 20:41.646
And as a result of that, they are doing some things 
that they might not ought to be doing.

20:42.537 --> 20:49.791
I wouldn't expect anybody to take this advice, but 
I think it's what colleges ought to do, is they

20:42.537 --> 20:49.791
shouldn't sell their souls in order to survive. If 
they can't survive doing what they are designed to

20:49.811 --> 20:56.083
do, then fold. Just go away. Now, that's contrary 
to what human nature is. But I think if we aren't

21:01.794 --> 21:03.617
careful, we'll try to do some things we shouldn't 
be doing, and we wind up not doing those well and

21:04.103 --> 21:10.089
getting in trouble. If I were going to advise the 
department, a lot of it goes back to what you and I

21:11.870 --> 21:17.836
have already talked about.

21:20.578 --> 21:28.866
I really think that we are much, much 
overemphasizing the exercise physiology

21:20.578 --> 21:28.866
component.

21:29.567 --> 21:30.988
They don't have a constituency. They're very good 
at what they're doing. They're conducting very

21:34.265 --> 21:36.990
good research. And as I said, we have the only two 
distinguished professors in the entire college.

21:42.700 --> 21:43.382
And they are good. I think their research would 
stand up with anybody's. But who are they doing it

21:46.848 --> 21:49.351
for? They can't, they don't have a constituency. 
They're doing it for the sake of reporting it in

21:53.134 --> 22:01.623
journals of which other exercise physiologists 
will read and do research and report to other

21:53.134 --> 22:01.623
exercise physiologists. And that pyramid's 
going to topple one of these days. We're, more and

22:05.888 --> 22:13.075
more we're charging students who are using the 
university We're putting more and more of the

22:13.342 --> 22:18.827
burden of paying for the university on them, less 
and less on the state. And the more we do that, the

22:18.847 --> 22:24.713
more critical the parents who are paying for the 
education are going to be. And one day they're

22:24.873 --> 22:27.356
going to look and say, what are we getting for our 
money? And I'm of the opinion right now that it's

22:28.817 --> 22:38.607
the worst investment they make, based on what, as 
an insider in the university, I think it's one of

22:28.817 --> 22:38.607
the worst investments they make. And that breaks 
my heart to say that. I wish I didn't believe that. I

22:43.086 --> 22:43.867
wish it weren't true. And hopefully it isn't true, 
but it sure feels that way. So I'd say to our

22:46.852 --> 22:56.367
department, we need to determine who our 
constituencies are and try to address their needs

22:46.852 --> 22:56.367
better than what we're doing right now. All right. 
Let's make believe someone walks up and gives you a

23:01.555 --> 23:06.383
check for a million dollars with one condition. 
You must pass it on to Texas A&M, but you've got to

23:07.088 --> 23:11.232
decide the use of that money. If you could make a 
truly meaningful gift to this institution, for

23:12.093 --> 23:16.977
what purpose would you give that?

23:22.362 --> 23:25.785
There's just a bunch of them, obviously.

23:28.548 --> 23:34.193
You're asking me now to be magnanimous, and I don't 
know if I could be.

23:47.386 --> 24:06.967
Well,

23:47.386 --> 24:06.967
I guess what I think, I don't know if this would be 
the answer I'd give or not, but it addresses a need

23:47.386 --> 24:06.967
that's consistent with what I just said. The cost 
of going to school is greater now than it's ever

24:07.007 --> 24:16.617
been, and I fear that a lot of people are being cut 
out now for reasons that they never were cut out

24:17.086 --> 24:20.469
before. When I came to school, money was not going 
to keep me from going to college. My ability and

24:24.253 --> 24:29.478
willingness to study might, but I could probably 
make it. I could sell eggs and make it. But that's

24:33.922 --> 24:35.043
not true anymore. So I guess I would encourage that 
person to put them into scholarships that

24:35.643 --> 24:41.629
students could. What kind of students would you 
want to receive these scholarships? Well, I don't

24:46.263 --> 24:54.412
think I would, again, this is consistent with what 
my beliefs is, I wouldn't want them to become the

24:46.263 --> 24:54.412
elite student. I wouldn't want them to go to the 
